{
  "text_id": "oracc.etcsri.Q001091",
  "corpus": "oracc",
  "title": "En-metena 17 (RIME 1.09.05.17 composite)",
  "language": "sumerian",
  "translation_source": "ORACC ETCSRI — CC BY-SA 3.0",
  "source_url": "https://oracc.museum.upenn.edu/etcsri/Q001091",
  "paragraphs": [
    {
      "para_id": "Q001091.1",
      "line_range": "1",
      "translation": "(shoulder i 1) En-metena , ruler of Lagaš , parceled out 25 bur of land , ( a field called ) En-ana-tum-sur-Nanše-etaed , 11 bur of land , ( a field called ) Nizuh-šub in the marshland of Niĝin , next to the holy canal , and 60 bur of land , ( a field called ) Enlil in the area of Gu-edena for Enlil of the E-adda ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001091.13",
      "line_range": "13",
      "translation": "(statue i 1) For Enlil of the E-adda ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001091.15",
      "line_range": "15",
      "translation": "(statue i 3) En-metena , ruler of Lagaš , chosen by Nanše in the heart , chief governor of Ninĝirsu , child of En-ana-tum , ruler of Lagaš , descendant of Ur-Nanše , king of Lagaš , built the sanctuary of Dugru for Ninĝirsu , built him the A-huš , the temple that is looked upon with favour ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001091.35",
      "line_range": "35",
      "translation": "(statue ii 3) For Lugal-uruba , he built his great temple in Urub ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001091.38",
      "line_range": "38",
      "translation": "(statue ii 6) For Nanše , he built the E-engur in Zulum ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001091.41",
      "line_range": "41",
      "translation": "(statue ii 9) For Enki , king of Eridug , he built the Abzu-pasira ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001091.45",
      "line_range": "45",
      "translation": "(statue ii 13) For Ninhursaĝa , he built the high temple of Tirkug ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001091.49",
      "line_range": "49",
      "translation": "(statue ii 17) For Ninĝirsu , he built the Antasura ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001091.52",
      "line_range": "52",
      "translation": "(statue ii 20) For ( Nanše ) , he built the Šage-pada ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001091.54",
      "line_range": "54",
      "translation": "(statue ii 22) He built the temple of Ĝatumdug ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001091.56",
      "line_range": "56",
      "translation": "(statue iii 1) For Nanše , he built her lofty high temple and restored her temple ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001091.60",
      "line_range": "60",
      "translation": "(statue iii 5) For Enlil , he built the E-adda in Imsaĝ ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001091.63",
      "line_range": "63",
      "translation": "(statue iii 8) At that time , En-metena fashioned his ( own ) statue , named him \" En-metena is the beloved of Enlil \", and brought it before Enlil in the temple ."
    },
    {
      "para_id": "Q001091.71",
      "line_range": "71",
      "translation": "(statue iv 2) May Šul-MUŠxPA , the personal god of En-metena , the builder of the E-adda , pay obeisance to Enlil perpetually for the well-being of En-metena , ruler of Lagaš !"
    }
  ],
